    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-12-26T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-12-26T05:00:00-05:00" n="369"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d369">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.5048/375: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-12-26T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 26, 1930—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 26—7:37 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Consulate’s December 18, 9 a.m.<note n="55" xml:id="d369fn55">Not printed.</note>
                    Am informed that League has received formal note from British Government
                    requesting that Liberian inquiry report be placed on the agenda of the next
                    meeting of the Council. In order to be placed on the agenda, action is required
                    by the Council at its first meeting. This action, however, is regarded as merely
                        <hi rend="italic">pro forma.</hi>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
